    "recipeIngredient": [
        "2 cups all-purpose flour, plus more for rolling",
        "0.5 teaspoon baking powder",
        "0.25 teaspoon salt",
        "0.5 cup (1 stick) unsalted butter, room temperature",
        "1 cup granulated sugar",
        "1 large egg",
        "1 teaspoon vanilla extract",
        "Assorted candies, sprinkles, or colored sugars, for decorating (optional)",
        "1.5 cup confectioners' sugar",
        "3-4 tablespoons milk, water, or lemon juice"
    ],
    "recipeInstructions": [
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.marthastewart.com/thmb/w8bB0xvnp65eswvUo7Rh4FqpWJ8=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/MSL-338471-Basic-Sugar-Cookies-Step-1-0923-7e7981996c5d40e59c080b71392d0e06.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Whisk together dry ingredients: In large bowl, whisk flour, baking powder, and salt."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.marthastewart.com/thmb/1gKznjWImyR2byKUVuPQW0C5F3k=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/MSL-338471-Basic-Sugar-Cookies-Step-2-0923-5eb88df4a2c24be49e056dcc8f045ddd.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Cream butter and sugar: With an electric mixer, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.marthastewart.com/thmb/zbzm9lj-yreIb6mcQs8uV0YI6MI=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/MSL-338471-Basic-Sugar-Cookies-Step-3-0923-e55b463db56a49419a5155e7be47c11c.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Add egg and vanilla: Beat in egg and vanilla."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.marthastewart.com/thmb/nkKJIeqb3DLezdYevtYnMyLIAhE=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/MSL-338471-Basic-Sugar-Cookies-Step-4-0923-d8f950c690c844db8194fb6f1f319e93.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Add dry ingredients: With mixer on low, gradually add flour mixture; beat until combined."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.marthastewart.com/thmb/T7SvBKCJEfZXa0hYJB9CVyVvDZk=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/MSL-338471-Basic-Sugar-Cookies-Step-5-0923-0c897409800b4dee97497df164855d27.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Chill dough: Divide dough in half; flatten into disks. Wrap each half in plastic; freeze until firm, at least 20 minutes, or place in a resealable plastic bag, and freeze up to 3 months (thaw in refrigerator overnight)."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.marthastewart.com/thmb/ZRT28XlqCnLW63_3zy9FUVqKtYc=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/MSL-338471-Basic-Sugar-Cookies-Step-6-0923-69fa9c40f35d40439150cd5a9e8e5134.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Roll out dough and cut cookie shapes: Preheat oven to 325Â°F. Line baking sheets with parchment. Remove one dough disk; let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Roll out 1/8 inch thick between two sheets of floured parchment, dusting dough with flour as needed."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.marthastewart.com/thmb/FoFQIP7GNceqWRPFBZyqJt88cT0=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/MSL-338471-Basic-Sugar-Cookies-Step-7-b-0923-e0c1b0f5ccf746a4a3804f49a5f8bbef.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Cut out cookies: Cut shapes with cookie cutters."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.marthastewart.com/thmb/JsqY0LC5N1ThbFnY2_AU4oHalII=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/MSL-338471-Basic-Sugar-Cookies-Step-8-0923-de01e5b0c9364cab9ae0cb389bc6fb8a.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Place cookies on baking sheets: Using a spatula, transfer to prepared baking sheets. (If dough gets soft, chill 10 minutes.) Reroll scraps; cut shapes. Repeat with remaining dough."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.marthastewart.com/thmb/0EiA2_UN60FHDE7UWcHo8DBJ1U4=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/MSL-338471-Basic-Sugar-Cookies-Step-9-0923-81a3aed7916a4c7e88ffc385c7ecc26b.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Bake cookies and let cool: Bake, rotating halfway through, until edges are golden, 10 to 18 minutes (depending on size). Cool completely on wire racks."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.marthastewart.com/thmb/u5gF3EzZ6EWA3K_SqvfBZxiwrgA=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/MSL-338471-Basic-Sugar-Cookies-Step-10-b-0923-6db7422c454a4f79997736174e6b6b64.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Make icing Sift confectioners&#39; sugar into a small bowl. Whisk in milk, water, or lemon juice, 1 tablespoon at a time, until smooth and thick enough to coat the back of a spoon. If too thin, whisk in more sugar; if too thick, add more liquid."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.marthastewart.com/thmb/5hgAt8ZYp9us9ioAsI0Cl5jS71Y=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/MSL-338471-Basic-Sugar-Cookies-Step-11-0923-50b0000d13984970b321ee13ad049b71.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Decorate cookies: Dip cookies in icing or spread icing over cookies using the back of a spoon. Add other decorations, if desired. Let the icing harden, about 20 minutes."
        }
    ],
